b1 10% confluent. Wash the cells once with <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> and add mTeSR\u21221 medium to the well. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"9EE38D6038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":2,"type_id":25,"title":"concentration","source":{"concentration":1,"unit":null,"title":"PBS w\/o Ca2+ and Mg2+"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":[{"id":5,"title":"Wash","icon":"WashIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089270,"guid":"454AFF9038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089277,"previous_guid":"B9D374F038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4EB2DF8CFF924CF0967FBE7F79DF345F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"61B35F9012B4418A89126CF878634778","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For titration and copy number determination, we perform a qPCR on genomic DNA to count the number of integrated viral particles (WPRE) relative to the genome (albumin gene). Wait at least <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> before isolating genomic DNA using a genomicDNAextraction kit, such as the DNeasy\u00ae Blood and Tissue Kit (Qiagen), according to the manufacturer\u2019s instructions. The DNA should be placed <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> if used immediately or stored at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"B101665053BF11EBAA3BD5FD4DC9E2D9","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":345600,"title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"ED88EA0038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":0,"unit":"On ice","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"F2C4068038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":-20,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":345600},{"id":1089271,"guid":"4AD8F70038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089270,"previous_guid":"454AFF9038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F1AC5CCED91645E2A18ADFE2DA030033","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"CB8315D0B5FF4E2CA3B8E19225164FA6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Adjust the concentration of the pAlbumin plasmid used for normalization to <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>, which corresponds to 1.2 \u00d7 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">11<\/span><span> molecules\/\u03bcl (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">see<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note 22<\/span><span>). Prepare a standard curve, with the first point being 1 \u00d7 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">7<\/span><span> molecules in 8 \u03bcl (which corresponds to 1.25 \u00d7 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span> molecules\/\u03bcl). Prepare the other points of the standard curve by serial tenfold dilutions until there are ten molecules in 8 \u03bcl (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">see<\/span><span> Fig. 3c). <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"0210A6C038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":2,"type_id":25,"title":"concentration","source":{"concentration":1,"unit":null,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089272,"guid":"4F19FC1038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089271,"previous_guid":"4AD8F70038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"93F1C058B20045439A00F1B77AE508BA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B186480772204B7EBEF7191613E1B86B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare two master mixes of <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, and <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> per sample including all samples and standards in duplicates (one master mix with albumin primers and probe for genomic DNA detection and one with WPRE primers and probe for lentivirus detection). <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"97EC257038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":8.5,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":"TaqMan\u00ae Universal PCR Master Mix"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"9DC41E3038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":0.17,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":"forward primer (10 \u03bcM)"}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"A3D4DA3038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":4,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":0.17,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":"reverse primer (10 \u03bcM)"}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"AC7568D038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":5,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":0.17,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":"probe (10 \u03bcM)"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":[{"id":6,"title":"Mix","icon":"MixIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089273,"guid":"53622D1038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089281,"previous_guid":"F76B2AF038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"769EB5991C414DC3BBC34E426143823E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"894A52028F7D4FC58E61F705FE206AF4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Plot the standard curve using the software of your qPCR machine or manually using other software such as Microsoft Excel, and calculate the quantity of albumin and WPRE for each sample using the equation of the standard curve.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":[{"id":10,"title":"Computational Step","icon":"ComputationalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089274,"guid":"56DB4E4038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089273,"previous_guid":"53622D1038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9C02B791A0DD4D018F49F576237B2858","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3974FD5F972F450992C8CEFF8104CE85","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Calculate the copy number for each sample as follows: Copy number = (quantity mean of WPRE sequence\/quantity mean of Alb sequence) \u00d7 2.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089275,"guid":"59D0C08038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089274,"previous_guid":"56DB4E4038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"BE959DD0C12D4EFBB03BA3228C721175","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"86AF7412C95F458CAF22EE9F304D72F5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Calculate the viral titer with the following formula: Titer (viral genome\/ml) = (number of target cells counted at day 1 \u00d7 number of copies per cell of the sample)\/volume of supernatant (ml).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089276,"guid":"AB1C0FD038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089269,"previous_guid":"3ED84D7038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B84067614B674BCDBC66F8E361C7A866","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"EA1F073DEEA54F8E94B3511D54E1085C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Add mTeSR\u21221 to the tube containing the virus suspension, mix gently and transfer dropwise to one or more wells (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">see<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note 20<\/span><span>).<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":[{"id":6,"title":"Mix","icon":"MixIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089277,"guid":"B9D374F038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089276,"previous_guid":"AB1C0FD038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"74DD720A2C874BE4BAB796733CE87EF2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"09ADAE51CE004FA8B8D16B322F5B3935","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate the culture dish <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> and change the medium on the next day (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">see<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note 21<\/span><span>). Starting 48 h after transduction, select for cells with an integrated construct with the appropriate antibiotic (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">see<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note 14<\/span><span>).<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"BE60772038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":30,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":[{"id":1,"title":"Incubation","icon":"IncubationIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":30},{"id":1089279,"guid":"B3901AC038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089272,"previous_guid":"4F19FC1038D311EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8D050BE31CAF4A5B9CA338A68A1ECD86","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0A33E0E67CA14369BA86417DBEC55C9D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Aliquot <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> per well of a 96-well plate and add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> (concentration between <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> and <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> in <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">). <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"BCD4FFB038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":9,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":"master mix"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"C3A7AC2038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":8,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":"sample DNA"}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"DCBC440038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":4,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":50,"unit":"ng","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"D68D51A038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":5,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":100,"unit":"ng","title":"DNA"}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"D92B06F038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":6,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":8,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089280,"guid":"E7FB725038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089279,"previous_guid":"B3901AC038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E6F12F64B8014CD3B11AC9947AE2E0EC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"699229E9FCD24A05BA3DBA07735E5F7E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Seal the plate, carefully mix by vortexing and briefly spin down. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":[{"id":2,"title":"Centrifugation","icon":"CentrifugationIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1089281,"guid":"F76B2AF038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","previous_id":1089280,"previous_guid":"E7FB725038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"012F8AEC0DB7463B8BE321DC3DC79DE0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Lentivirus Production and Transduction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5104454FB081496381B5F28981E4FBF1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Run the qPCR with the settings for FAM fluorochromes and BHQ quenchers with the following program: 1 cycle of <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> followed by 50 cycles of <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> and <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">see<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\"> <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note 17<\/span><span>). <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"FD53505038D411EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":600,"title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"00E8850038D511EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":95,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"03FE9EA038D511EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":4,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":15,"title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"05B91FE038D511EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":5,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":95,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"0A3A624038D511EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":6,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":60,"title":""}},{"id":1054730,"guid":"0EC58FB038D511EB98E623DAF65FC66F","order_id":7,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":60,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":523655,"critical":[{"id":4,"title":"PCR","icon":"PCRIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":675}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This is part 3.3 of the \"<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/private\/C65DB81838BC11EBA61A0A58A9FEAC2A\/protocols\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Induced Neurons for the Study of Neurodegenerative and Neurodevelopmental Disorders<\/span><\/a><span>\" collection of protocols.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Collection Abstract:<\/span><span> Patient-derived or genomically modified human induced pluripotent stem cells (iPSCs) offer the opportunity to study neurodevelopmental and neurodegenerative disorders. Overexpression of certain neurogenic transcription factors (TFs) in iPSCs can induce efficient differentiation into homogeneous populations of the disease-relevant neuronal cell types. Here we provide protocols for genomic manipulations of iPSCs by CRISPR\/Cas9. We also introduce two methods, based on lentiviral delivery and the piggyBac transposon system, to stably integrate neurogenic TFs into human iPSCs. Furthermore, we describe the TF-mediated neuronal differentiation and maturation in combination with astrocyte cocultures.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1630617673}